Photo by Travis Lubinsky in Hollywood, California with @danfleyshman, @tombrady, and @thecoffeebreakers. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, wrist watch and indoor.

node.text:
I’m at a loss for words. @danfleyshman just blessed me with a @tombrady Rookie Card PSA 9.5! 

When Dan told me about his idea for @thecoffeebreakers, I knew it was going to be a success, but I didn’t realize he would break $11,000,000 in sales in 9 months 🤯 

Congratulations to @danfleyshman @djskee and the entire team.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travis Lubinsky in Pacific Beach with @flexwatches, and @palmys. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
The plan was to create something special in Pacific Beach San Diego, a city that gave us so many good memories. In college I used to eat at a café at 976 Felspar, which is now @palmys!

Over the past few months, a team of rockstars came together to launch a breakfast and lunch joint unlike any other in San Diego. I can’t wait to enjoy a fresh Açaí bowl and a hot coffee on the patio very soon!!!

Get ready to see some familiar faces at @palmys. You will see pro skaters, surfers and local tastemakers. 

Stay tuned for details on the opening 🌴

#sandiego #pacificbeach #restaurante

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travis Lubinsky on July 25, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
I was 18 years old and full of dreams! 

Shortly after this photo was taken, I started an apparel manufacturing company at SDSU and my career began. 

I managed Dj’s, hosted fashion shows, built websites, partnered with celebrities, and eventually became the co-founder of @flexwatches 

This lead me to appearing on TV over a dozen times, running an e-commerce portfolio, and creating partnerships with companies like Shopify, WWE, and Disney. 

These days I am managing a portfolio that includes several e-commerce brands, a creative agency, a media group, real estate and a new restaurant - @palmys 

The bottom line is that nobody is an overnight success story. You have to put in the work and be patient. Don’t believe what you see on Instagram. 

I still don’t consider myself to be “successful”, but the 18 year old Trav would be proud of the journey.
